page.title: 01Landscape in East Yorkshire
page.content: The chalk hills of the Yorkshire Wolds rise to 120 metres,dipping to the lay sea cliffs. arming. In East Yorkshire there is open country where farmers grow wheat,barley and oil seed rape which is a yellow colour.The farmers in this area of land keep cattle of all kinds but mostly dairy cattle. {Villages.}The two main villages are Hunmanby and Muston.Hunmanby is larger than Muston with around 2600 people and still expanding.In Hunmanby there are few farms and a Private School.Muston is a small village of around 300 people. {Tourism.}In East Yorkshire there are a lot of attractions for tourists. Butlins Holiday Camp recently closed,Primrose Valley caravan site, just outside Filey.The railway line in E.Yorks runs from Hull to Scarboro'._
